**Agreement, Roles, and Design Value**

1. Project Title: *Echoes of Partition*  
2. Roles (all taken by me as this will be an individual project)  
   1. Creative Director: Concept development, visual design, and storytelling elements  
   2. Technical Designer: TouchDesigner programming, projection mapping, and hardware setup  
   3. Sound Designer: Curate and edit ambient and historical audio  
   4. Researcher/Writer: Conduct historical research and craft the narrative foundation  
3. GitHub Repo: [https://github.com/humnahh/IMD-Capstone](https://github.com/humnahh/IMD-Capstone)

**Team Agreements**

This agreement is  aimed at creating  a work method  where  each team member  knows the production requirements  These  may vary over time according to the production development:  There may be stages where the workload will be higher for the conceptual directors,  and in other stages, the tech and programming team will have to kick it with more time investment than in the early stages.   
   
This agreement aims to establish a working relationship  and timeframe where each of you knows your time requirement for individual work, as well as for  group meetings  and decision making. 

*   ***Goal*** :   What is the purpose of the team which unifies you?   

The purposes of my project are: 

* To use immersive media to create an emotionally resonant storytelling experience about the Partition and its intergenerational impact.  
* Experiment with interactive projection design and TouchDesigner to visualize history and memory as a living, shifting entity.  
* Explore how personal narrative and collective history intersect through technology.  
* Strengthen my skills in interactive design, projection mapping, motion tracking, and sound integration.  
* Educate various audiences on the Partition, British colonialism, and South Asian history.  
* Preserve my family’s history and that of many others.

*    ***Decision   Making*** :  Does everyone have to agree  before making any change to the project?  What happens in case of a disagreement?  Is there a  director who is in charge of the overall vision, and therefore gets to make the final decision based on the input of each member? 

Since this is a personal/individual project, I will be the only one making decisions.

